The paper discusses the practice of Continuous Experimentation in the context of cyber-physical systems, which involves software development and deployment in systems that interact with the physical world. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Robotics (cs.RO), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Embedded Systems (cs.EM), or Cybernetics (cs.CY) categories. However, since the paper focuses on the software development aspect, cs.SE is the most likely category. The other categories are also relevant due to the physical interaction aspect, but to a lesser extent.
